8 // ----
9 // This pass performs loop invariant code motion on machine instructions. We ----
10 // attempt to remove as much code from the body of a loop as possible. ----
11 // ----
12 // This pass is not intended to be a replacement or a complete alternative ----
13 // for the LLVM-IR-level LICM pass. It is only designed to hoist simple ----
14 // constructs that are not exposed before lowering and instruction selection. ----
15 // ----
16 //===----------------------------------------------------------------------===// ----
17 ----

317 /// Test if the given loop is the outer-most loop that has a unique predecessor. ----
318 static bool LoopIsOuterMostWithPredecessor(MachineLoop *CurLoop) { 0
319 // Check whether this loop even has a unique predecessor. ----
320 if (!CurLoop->getLoopPredecessor()) 0
321 return false; 0
322 // Ok, now check to see if any of its outer loops do. ----
323 for (MachineLoop *L = CurLoop->getParentLoop(); L; L = L->getParentLoop()) 0
324 if (L->getLoopPredecessor()) 0
325 return false; 0
326 // None of them did, so this is the outermost with a unique predecessor. ----
327 return true; 0
328 } ----

330 bool MachineLICMBase::runOnMachineFunction(MachineFunction &MF) { 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
331 if (skipFunction(MF.getFunction())) 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
332 return false; 4 ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips_dbg.ll ../DebugInfoTest/example_mips.ll
333 ----
334 Changed = FirstInLoop = false; 0
335 const TargetSubtargetInfo &ST = MF.getSubtarget(); 0
336 TII = ST.getInstrInfo(); 0
337 TLI = ST.getTargetLowering(); 0
338 TRI = ST.getRegisterInfo(); 0
339 MFI = &MF.getFrameInfo(); 0
340 MRI = &MF.getRegInfo(); 0
341 SchedModel.init(&ST); 0
342 ----
343 PreRegAlloc = MRI->isSSA(); 0
344 HasProfileData = MF.getFunction().hasProfileData(); 0
345 ----
346 if (PreRegAlloc) 0
347 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "******** Pre-regalloc Machine LICM: "); 0
348 else ----
349 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "******** Post-regalloc Machine LICM: "); 0
350 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << MF.getName() << " ********\n"); 0
351 ----
352 if (PreRegAlloc) { 0
353 // Estimate register pressure during pre-regalloc pass. ----
354 unsigned NumRPS = TRI->getNumRegPressureSets(); 0
355 RegPressure.resize(NumRPS); 0
356 std::fill(RegPressure.begin(), RegPressure.end(), 0); 0
357 RegLimit.resize(NumRPS); 0
358 for (unsigned i = 0, e = NumRPS; i != e; ++i) 0
359 RegLimit[i] = TRI->getRegPressureSetLimit(MF, i); 0
360 } ----
361 ----
362 // Get our Loop information... ----
363 if (DisableHoistingToHotterBlocks != UseBFI::None) 0
364 MBFI = &getAnalysis(); 0
365 MLI = &getAnalysis(); 0
366 DT = &getAnalysis(); 0
367 AA = &getAnalysis().getAAResults(); 0
368 ----
369 SmallVector Worklist(MLI->begin(), MLI->end()); 0
370 while (!Worklist.empty()) { 0
371 CurLoop = Worklist.pop_back_val(); 0
372 CurPreheader = nullptr; 0
373 ExitBlocks.clear(); 0
374 ----
375 // If this is done before regalloc, only visit outer-most preheader-sporting ----
376 // loops. ----
377 if (PreRegAlloc && !LoopIsOuterMostWithPredecessor(CurLoop)) { 0
378 Worklist.append(CurLoop->begin(), CurLoop->end()); 0
379 continue; 0
380 } ----
381 ----
382 CurLoop->getExitBlocks(ExitBlocks); 0
383 ----
384 if (!PreRegAlloc) 0
385 HoistRegionPostRA(); 0
386 else { ----
387 // CSEMap is initialized for loop header when the first instruction is ----
388 // being hoisted. ----
389 MachineDomTreeNode *N = DT->getNode(CurLoop->getHeader()); 0
390 FirstInLoop = true; 0
391 HoistOutOfLoop(N); 0
392 CSEMap.clear(); 0
393 } ----
394 } ----
395 ----
396 return Changed; 0
397 } 0

399 /// Return true if instruction stores to the specified frame. ----
400 static bool InstructionStoresToFI(const MachineInstr *MI, int FI) { 0
401 // Check mayStore before memory operands so that e.g. DBG_VALUEs will return ----
402 // true since they have no memory operands. ----
403 if (!MI->mayStore()) 0
404 return false; 0
405 // If we lost memory operands, conservatively assume that the instruction ----
406 // writes to all slots. ----
407 if (MI->memoperands_empty()) 0
408 return true; 0
409 for (const MachineMemOperand *MemOp : MI->memoperands()) { 0
410 if (!MemOp->isStore() || !MemOp->getPseudoValue()) 0
411 continue; 0
412 if (const FixedStackPseudoSourceValue *Value = 0
413 dyn_cast(MemOp->getPseudoValue())) { 0
414 if (Value->getFrameIndex() == FI) 0
415 return true; 0
416 } ----
417 } ----
418 return false; 0
419 } ----

421 /// Examine the instruction for potentai LICM candidate. Also ----
422 /// gather register def and frame object update information. ----
423 void MachineLICMBase::ProcessMI(MachineInstr *MI, 0
424 BitVector &PhysRegDefs, ----
425 BitVector &PhysRegClobbers, ----
426 SmallSet &StoredFIs, ----
427 SmallVectorImpl &Candidates) { ----
428 bool RuledOut = false; 0
429 bool HasNonInvariantUse = false; 0
430 unsigned Def = 0; 0
431 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI->operands()) { 0
432 if (MO.isFI()) { 0
433 // Remember if the instruction stores to the frame index. ----
434 int FI = MO.getIndex(); 0
435 if (!StoredFIs.count(FI) && 0
436 MFI->isSpillSlotObjectIndex(FI) && 0
437 InstructionStoresToFI(MI, FI)) 0
438 StoredFIs.insert(FI); 0
439 HasNonInvariantUse = true; 0
440 continue; 0
441 } 0
442 ----
443 // We can't hoist an instruction defining a physreg that is clobbered in ----
444 // the loop. ----
445 if (MO.isRegMask()) { 0
446 PhysRegClobbers.setBitsNotInMask(MO.getRegMask()); 0
447 continue; 0
448 } ----
449 ----
450 if (!MO.isReg()) 0
451 continue; 0
452 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
453 if (!Reg) 0
454 continue; 0
455 assert(Reg.isPhysical() && "Not expecting virtual register!"); 0
456 ----
457 if (!MO.isDef()) { 0
458 if (Reg && (PhysRegDefs.test(Reg) || PhysRegClobbers.test(Reg))) 0
459 // If it's using a non-loop-invariant register, then it's obviously not ----
460 // safe to hoist. ----
461 HasNonInvariantUse = true; 0
462 continue; 0
463 } ----
464 ----
465 if (MO.isImplicit()) { 0
466 for (MCRegAliasIterator AI(Reg, TRI, true); AI.isValid(); ++AI) 0
467 PhysRegClobbers.set(*AI); 0
468 if (!MO.isDead()) 0
469 // Non-dead implicit def? This cannot be hoisted. ----
470 RuledOut = true; 0
471 // No need to check if a dead implicit def is also defined by ----
472 // another instruction. ----
473 continue; 0
474 } 0
475 ----
476 // FIXME: For now, avoid instructions with multiple defs, unless ----
477 // it's a dead implicit def. ----
478 if (Def) 0
479 RuledOut = true; 0
480 else ----
481 Def = Reg; 0
482 ----
483 // If we have already seen another instruction that defines the same ----
484 // register, then this is not safe. Two defs is indicated by setting a ----
485 // PhysRegClobbers bit. ----
486 for (MCRegAliasIterator AS(Reg, TRI, true); AS.isValid(); ++AS) { 0
487 if (PhysRegDefs.test(*AS)) 0
488 PhysRegClobbers.set(*AS); 0
489 } ----
490 // Need a second loop because MCRegAliasIterator can visit the same ----
491 // register twice. ----
492 for (MCRegAliasIterator AS(Reg, TRI, true); AS.isValid(); ++AS) 0
493 PhysRegDefs.set(*AS); 0
494 ----
495 if (PhysRegClobbers.test(Reg)) 0
496 // MI defined register is seen defined by another instruction in ----
497 // the loop, it cannot be a LICM candidate. ----
498 RuledOut = true; 0
499 } ----
500 ----
501 // Only consider reloads for now and remats which do not have register ----
502 // operands. FIXME: Consider unfold load folding instructions. ----
503 if (Def && !RuledOut) { 0
504 int FI = std::numeric_limits::min(); 0
505 if ((!HasNonInvariantUse && IsLICMCandidate(*MI)) || 0
506 (TII->isLoadFromStackSlot(*MI, FI) && MFI->isSpillSlotObjectIndex(FI))) 0
507 Candidates.push_back(CandidateInfo(MI, Def, FI)); 0
508 } ----
509 } 0
510 ----
511 /// Walk the specified region of the CFG and hoist loop invariants out to the ----
512 /// preheader. ----
513 void MachineLICMBase::HoistRegionPostRA() { 0
514 MachineBasicBlock *Preheader = getCurPreheader(); 0
515 if (!Preheader) 0
516 return; 0
517 ----
518 unsigned NumRegs = TRI->getNumRegs(); 0
519 BitVector PhysRegDefs(NumRegs); // Regs defined once in the loop. 0
520 BitVector PhysRegClobbers(NumRegs); // Regs defined more than once. 0
521 ----
522 SmallVector Candidates; 0
523 SmallSet StoredFIs; 0
524 ----
525 // Walk the entire region, count number of defs for each register, and ----
526 // collect potential LICM candidates. ----
527 for (MachineBasicBlock *BB : CurLoop->getBlocks()) { 0
528 // If the header of the loop containing this basic block is a landing pad, ----
529 // then don't try to hoist instructions out of this loop. ----
530 const MachineLoop *ML = MLI->getLoopFor(BB); 0
531 if (ML && ML->getHeader()->isEHPad()) continue; 0
532 ----
533 // Conservatively treat live-in's as an external def. ----
534 // FIXME: That means a reload that're reused in successor block(s) will not ----
535 // be LICM'ed. ----
536 for (const auto &LI : BB->liveins()) { 0
537 for (MCRegAliasIterator AI(LI.PhysReg, TRI, true); AI.isValid(); ++AI) 0
538 PhysRegDefs.set(*AI); 0
539 } ----
540 ----
541 SpeculationState = SpeculateUnknown; 0
542 for (MachineInstr &MI : *BB) 0
543 ProcessMI(&MI, PhysRegDefs, PhysRegClobbers, StoredFIs, Candidates); 0
544 } ----
545 ----
546 // Gather the registers read / clobbered by the terminator. ----
547 BitVector TermRegs(NumRegs); 0
548 MachineBasicBlock::iterator TI = Preheader->getFirstTerminator(); 0
549 if (TI != Preheader->end()) { 0
550 for (const MachineOperand &MO : TI->operands()) { 0
551 if (!MO.isReg()) 0
552 continue; 0
553 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
554 if (!Reg) 0
555 continue; 0
556 for (MCRegAliasIterator AI(Reg, TRI, true); AI.isValid(); ++AI) 0
557 TermRegs.set(*AI); 0
558 } ----
559 } ----
560 ----
561 // Now evaluate whether the potential candidates qualify. ----
562 // 1. Check if the candidate defined register is defined by another ----
563 // instruction in the loop. ----
564 // 2. If the candidate is a load from stack slot (always true for now), ----
565 // check if the slot is stored anywhere in the loop. ----
566 // 3. Make sure candidate def should not clobber ----
567 // registers read by the terminator. Similarly its def should not be ----
568 // clobbered by the terminator. ----
569 for (CandidateInfo &Candidate : Candidates) { 0
570 if (Candidate.FI != std::numeric_limits::min() && 0
571 StoredFIs.count(Candidate.FI)) 0
572 continue; 0
573 ----
574 unsigned Def = Candidate.Def; 0
575 if (!PhysRegClobbers.test(Def) && !TermRegs.test(Def)) { 0
576 bool Safe = true; 0
577 MachineInstr *MI = Candidate.MI; 0
578 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI->all_uses()) { 0
579 if (!MO.getReg()) 0
580 continue; 0
581 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
582 if (PhysRegDefs.test(Reg) || 0
583 PhysRegClobbers.test(Reg)) { 0
584 // If it's using a non-loop-invariant register, then it's obviously ----
585 // not safe to hoist. ----
586 Safe = false; 0
587 break; 0
588 } ----
589 } ----
590 if (Safe) 0
591 HoistPostRA(MI, Candidate.Def); 0
592 } ----
593 } ----
594 } 0
595 ----
596 /// Add register 'Reg' to the livein sets of BBs in the current loop, and make ----
597 /// sure it is not killed by any instructions in the loop. ----
598 void MachineLICMBase::AddToLiveIns(MCRegister Reg) { 0
599 for (MachineBasicBlock *BB : CurLoop->getBlocks()) { 0
600 if (!BB->isLiveIn(Reg)) 0
601 BB->addLiveIn(Reg); 0
602 for (MachineInstr &MI : *BB) { 0
603 for (MachineOperand &MO : MI.all_uses()) { 0
604 if (!MO.getReg()) 0
605 continue; 0
606 if (MO.getReg() == Reg || TRI->isSuperRegister(Reg, MO.getReg())) 0
607 MO.setIsKill(false); 0
608 } ----
609 } ----
610 } ----
611 } 0
612 ----
613 /// When an instruction is found to only use loop invariant operands that is ----
614 /// safe to hoist, this instruction is called to do the dirty work. ----
615 void MachineLICMBase::HoistPostRA(MachineInstr *MI, unsigned Def) { 0
616 MachineBasicBlock *Preheader = getCurPreheader(); 0
617 ----
618 // Now move the instructions to the predecessor, inserting it before any ----
619 // terminator instructions. ----
620 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Hoisting to " << printMBBReference(*Preheader) 0
621 << " from " << printMBBReference(*MI->getParent()) << ": " ----
622 << *MI); ----
623 ----
624 // Splice the instruction to the preheader. ----
625 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = MI->getParent(); 0
626 Preheader->splice(Preheader->getFirstTerminator(), MBB, MI); 0
627 ----
628 // Since we are moving the instruction out of its basic block, we do not ----
629 // retain its debug location. Doing so would degrade the debugging ----
630 // experience and adversely affect the accuracy of profiling information. ----
631 assert(!MI->isDebugInstr() && "Should not hoist debug inst"); 0
632 MI->setDebugLoc(DebugLoc()); 0
633 ----
634 // Add register to livein list to all the BBs in the current loop since a ----
635 // loop invariant must be kept live throughout the whole loop. This is ----
636 // important to ensure later passes do not scavenge the def register. ----
637 AddToLiveIns(Def); 0
638 ----
639 ++NumPostRAHoisted; 0
640 Changed = true; 0
641 } 0
642 ----
643 /// Check if this mbb is guaranteed to execute. If not then a load from this mbb ----
644 /// may not be safe to hoist. ----
645 bool MachineLICMBase::IsGuaranteedToExecute(MachineBasicBlock *BB) { 0
646 if (SpeculationState != SpeculateUnknown) 0
647 return SpeculationState == SpeculateFalse; 0
648 ----
649 if (BB != CurLoop->getHeader()) { 0
650 // Check loop exiting blocks. ----
651 SmallVector CurrentLoopExitingBlocks; 0
652 CurLoop->getExitingBlocks(CurrentLoopExitingBlocks); 0
653 for (MachineBasicBlock *CurrentLoopExitingBlock : CurrentLoopExitingBlocks) 0
654 if (!DT->dominates(BB, CurrentLoopExitingBlock)) { 0
655 SpeculationState = SpeculateTrue; 0
656 return false; 0
657 } ----
658 } 0
659 ----
660 SpeculationState = SpeculateFalse; 0
661 return true; 0
662 } ----
663 ----
664 /// Check if \p MI is trivially remateralizable and if it does not have any ----
665 /// virtual register uses. Even though rematerializable RA might not actually ----
666 /// rematerialize it in this scenario. In that case we do not want to hoist such ----
667 /// instruction out of the loop in a belief RA will sink it back if needed. ----
668 bool MachineLICMBase::isTriviallyReMaterializable( 0
669 const MachineInstr &MI) const { ----
670 if (!TII->isTriviallyReMaterializable(MI)) 0
671 return false; 0
672 ----
673 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI.all_uses()) { 0
674 if (MO.getReg().isVirtual()) 0
675 return false; 0
676 } ----
677 ----
678 return true; 0
679 } ----
680 ----
681 void MachineLICMBase::EnterScope(MachineBasicBlock *MBB) { 0
682 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Entering " << printMBBReference(*MBB) << '\n'); 0
683 ----
684 // Remember livein register pressure. ----
685 BackTrace.push_back(RegPressure); 0
686 } 0
687 ----
688 void MachineLICMBase::ExitScope(MachineBasicBlock *MBB) { 0
689 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Exiting " << printMBBReference(*MBB) << '\n'); 0
690 BackTrace.pop_back(); 0
691 } 0
692 ----
693 /// Destroy scope for the MBB that corresponds to the given dominator tree node ----
694 /// if its a leaf or all of its children are done. Walk up the dominator tree to ----
695 /// destroy ancestors which are now done. ----
696 void MachineLICMBase::ExitScopeIfDone(MachineDomTreeNode *Node, 0
697 DenseMap &OpenChildren, ----
698 const DenseMap &ParentMap) { ----
699 if (OpenChildren[Node]) 0
700 return; 0
701 ----
702 for(;;) { ----
703 ExitScope(Node->getBlock()); 0
704 // Now traverse upwards to pop ancestors whose offsprings are all done. ----
705 MachineDomTreeNode *Parent = ParentMap.lookup(Node); 0
706 if (!Parent || --OpenChildren[Parent] != 0) 0
707 break; 0
708 Node = Parent; 0
709 } 0
710 } ----
711 ----
712 /// Walk the specified loop in the CFG (defined by all blocks dominated by the ----
713 /// specified header block, and that are in the current loop) in depth first ----
714 /// order w.r.t the DominatorTree. This allows us to visit definitions before ----
715 /// uses, allowing us to hoist a loop body in one pass without iteration. ----
716 void MachineLICMBase::HoistOutOfLoop(MachineDomTreeNode *HeaderN) { 0
717 MachineBasicBlock *Preheader = getCurPreheader(); 0
718 if (!Preheader) 0
719 return; 0
720 ----
721 SmallVector Scopes; 0
722 SmallVector WorkList; 0
723 DenseMap ParentMap; 0
724 DenseMap OpenChildren; 0
725 ----
726 // Perform a DFS walk to determine the order of visit. ----
727 WorkList.push_back(HeaderN); 0
728 while (!WorkList.empty()) { 0
729 MachineDomTreeNode *Node = WorkList.pop_back_val(); 0
730 assert(Node && "Null dominator tree node?"); 0
731 MachineBasicBlock *BB = Node->getBlock(); 0
732 ----
733 // If the header of the loop containing this basic block is a landing pad, ----
734 // then don't try to hoist instructions out of this loop. ----
735 const MachineLoop *ML = MLI->getLoopFor(BB); 0
736 if (ML && ML->getHeader()->isEHPad()) 0
737 continue; 0
738 ----
739 // If this subregion is not in the top level loop at all, exit. ----
740 if (!CurLoop->contains(BB)) 0
741 continue; 0
742 ----
743 Scopes.push_back(Node); 0
744 unsigned NumChildren = Node->getNumChildren(); 0
745 ----
746 // Don't hoist things out of a large switch statement. This often causes ----
747 // code to be hoisted that wasn't going to be executed, and increases ----
748 // register pressure in a situation where it's likely to matter. ----
749 if (BB->succ_size() >= 25) 0
750 NumChildren = 0; 0
751 ----
752 OpenChildren[Node] = NumChildren; 0
753 if (NumChildren) { 0
754 // Add children in reverse order as then the next popped worklist node is ----
755 // the first child of this node. This means we ultimately traverse the ----
756 // DOM tree in exactly the same order as if we'd recursed. ----
757 for (MachineDomTreeNode *Child : reverse(Node->children())) { 0
758 ParentMap[Child] = Node; 0
759 WorkList.push_back(Child); 0
760 } ----
761 } ----
762 } ----
763 ----
764 if (Scopes.size() == 0) 0
765 return; 0
766 ----
767 // Compute registers which are livein into the loop headers. ----
768 RegSeen.clear(); 0
769 BackTrace.clear(); 0
770 InitRegPressure(Preheader); 0
771 ----
772 // Now perform LICM. ----
773 for (MachineDomTreeNode *Node : Scopes) { 0
774 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = Node->getBlock(); 0
775 ----
776 EnterScope(MBB); 0
777 ----
778 // Process the block ----
779 SpeculationState = SpeculateUnknown; 0
780 for (MachineInstr &MI : llvm::make_early_inc_range(*MBB)) { 0
781 if (!Hoist(&MI, Preheader)) 0
782 UpdateRegPressure(&MI); 0
783 // If we have hoisted an instruction that may store, it can only be a ----
784 // constant store. ----
785 } ----
786 ----
787 // If it's a leaf node, it's done. Traverse upwards to pop ancestors. ----
788 ExitScopeIfDone(Node, OpenChildren, ParentMap); 0
789 } ----
790 } 0
791 ----
792 static bool isOperandKill(const MachineOperand &MO, MachineRegisterInfo *MRI) { 0
793 return MO.isKill() || MRI->hasOneNonDBGUse(MO.getReg()); 0
794 } ----
795 ----
796 /// Find all virtual register references that are liveout of the preheader to ----
797 /// initialize the starting "register pressure". Note this does not count live ----
798 /// through (livein but not used) registers. ----
799 void MachineLICMBase::InitRegPressure(MachineBasicBlock *BB) { 0
800 std::fill(RegPressure.begin(), RegPressure.end(), 0); 0
801 ----
802 // If the preheader has only a single predecessor and it ends with a ----
803 // fallthrough or an unconditional branch, then scan its predecessor for live ----
804 // defs as well. This happens whenever the preheader is created by splitting ----
805 // the critical edge from the loop predecessor to the loop header. ----
806 if (BB->pred_size() == 1) { 0
807 MachineBasicBlock *TBB = nullptr, *FBB = nullptr; 0
808 SmallVector Cond; 0
809 if (!TII->analyzeBranch(*BB, TBB, FBB, Cond, false) && Cond.empty()) 0
810 InitRegPressure(*BB->pred_begin()); 0
811 } 0
812 ----
813 for (const MachineInstr &MI : *BB) 0
814 UpdateRegPressure(&MI, /*ConsiderUnseenAsDef=*/true); 0
815 } 0
816 ----
817 /// Update estimate of register pressure after the specified instruction. ----
818 void MachineLICMBase::UpdateRegPressure(const MachineInstr *MI, 0
819 bool ConsiderUnseenAsDef) { ----
820 auto Cost = calcRegisterCost(MI, /*ConsiderSeen=*/true, ConsiderUnseenAsDef); 0
821 for (const auto &RPIdAndCost : Cost) { 0
822 unsigned Class = RPIdAndCost.first; 0
823 if (static_cast(RegPressure[Class]) < -RPIdAndCost.second) 0
824 RegPressure[Class] = 0; 0
825 else ----
826 RegPressure[Class] += RPIdAndCost.second; 0
827 } ----
828 } 0
829 ----
830 /// Calculate the additional register pressure that the registers used in MI ----
831 /// cause. ----
832 /// ----
833 /// If 'ConsiderSeen' is true, updates 'RegSeen' and uses the information to ----
834 /// figure out which usages are live-ins. ----
835 /// FIXME: Figure out a way to consider 'RegSeen' from all code paths. ----
836 DenseMap ----
837 MachineLICMBase::calcRegisterCost(const MachineInstr *MI, bool ConsiderSeen, 0
838 bool ConsiderUnseenAsDef) { ----
839 DenseMap Cost; 0
840 if (MI->isImplicitDef()) 0
841 return Cost; 0
842 for (unsigned i = 0, e = MI->getDesc().getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) { 0
843 const MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(i); 0
844 if (!MO.isReg() || MO.isImplicit()) 0
845 continue; 0
846 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
847 if (!Reg.isVirtual()) 0
848 continue; 0
849 ----
850 // FIXME: It seems bad to use RegSeen only for some of these calculations. ----
851 bool isNew = ConsiderSeen ? RegSeen.insert(Reg).second : false; 0
852 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = MRI->getRegClass(Reg); 0
853 ----
854 RegClassWeight W = TRI->getRegClassWeight(RC); 0
855 int RCCost = 0; 0
856 if (MO.isDef()) 0
857 RCCost = W.RegWeight; 0
858 else { ----
859 bool isKill = isOperandKill(MO, MRI); 0
860 if (isNew && !isKill && ConsiderUnseenAsDef) 0
861 // Haven't seen this, it must be a livein. ----
862 RCCost = W.RegWeight; 0
863 else if (!isNew && isKill) 0
864 RCCost = -W.RegWeight; 0
865 } ----
866 if (RCCost == 0) 0
867 continue; 0
868 const int *PS = TRI->getRegClassPressureSets(RC); 0
869 for (; *PS != -1; ++PS) { 0
870 if (!Cost.contains(*PS)) 0
871 Cost[*PS] = RCCost; 0
872 else ----
873 Cost[*PS] += RCCost; 0
874 } ----
875 } ----
876 return Cost; 0
877 } ----
878 ----
879 /// Return true if this machine instruction loads from global offset table or ----
880 /// constant pool. ----
881 static bool mayLoadFromGOTOrConstantPool(MachineInstr &MI) { 0
882 assert(MI.mayLoad() && "Expected MI that loads!"); 0
883 ----
884 // If we lost memory operands, conservatively assume that the instruction ----
885 // reads from everything.. ----
886 if (MI.memoperands_empty()) 0
887 return true; 0
888 ----
889 for (MachineMemOperand *MemOp : MI.memoperands()) 0
890 if (const PseudoSourceValue *PSV = MemOp->getPseudoValue()) 0
891 if (PSV->isGOT() || PSV->isConstantPool()) 0
892 return true; 0
893 ----
894 return false; 0
895 } ----
896 ----
897 // This function iterates through all the operands of the input store MI and ----
898 // checks that each register operand statisfies isCallerPreservedPhysReg. ----
899 // This means, the value being stored and the address where it is being stored ----
900 // is constant throughout the body of the function (not including prologue and ----
901 // epilogue). When called with an MI that isn't a store, it returns false. ----
902 // A future improvement can be to check if the store registers are constant ----
903 // throughout the loop rather than throughout the funtion. ----
904 static bool isInvariantStore(const MachineInstr &MI, 0
905 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI, ----
906 const MachineRegisterInfo *MRI) { ----
907 ----
908 bool FoundCallerPresReg = false; 0
909 if (!MI.mayStore() || MI.hasUnmodeledSideEffects() || 0
910 (MI.getNumOperands() == 0)) 0
911 return false; 0
912 ----
913 // Check that all register operands are caller-preserved physical registers. ----
914 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI.operands()) { 0
915 if (MO.isReg()) { 0
916 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
917 // If operand is a virtual register, check if it comes from a copy of a ----
918 // physical register. ----
919 if (Reg.isVirtual()) 0
920 Reg = TRI->lookThruCopyLike(MO.getReg(), MRI); 0
921 if (Reg.isVirtual()) 0
922 return false; 0
923 if (!TRI->isCallerPreservedPhysReg(Reg.asMCReg(), *MI.getMF())) 0
924 return false; 0
925 else ----
926 FoundCallerPresReg = true; 0
927 } else if (!MO.isImm()) { 0
928 return false; 0
929 } ----
930 } ----
931 return FoundCallerPresReg; 0
932 } ----
933 ----
934 // Return true if the input MI is a copy instruction that feeds an invariant ----
935 // store instruction. This means that the src of the copy has to satisfy ----
936 // isCallerPreservedPhysReg and atleast one of it's users should satisfy ----
937 // isInvariantStore. ----
938 static bool isCopyFeedingInvariantStore(const MachineInstr &MI, 0
939 const MachineRegisterInfo *MRI, ----
940 const TargetRegisterInfo *TRI) { ----
941 ----
942 // FIXME: If targets would like to look through instructions that aren't ----
943 // pure copies, this can be updated to a query. ----
944 if (!MI.isCopy()) 0
945 return false; 0
946 ----
947 const MachineFunction *MF = MI.getMF(); 0
948 // Check that we are copying a constant physical register. ----
949 Register CopySrcReg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
950 if (CopySrcReg.isVirtual()) 0
951 return false; 0
952 ----
953 if (!TRI->isCallerPreservedPhysReg(CopySrcReg.asMCReg(), *MF)) 0
954 return false; 0
955 ----
956 Register CopyDstReg = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
957 // Check if any of the uses of the copy are invariant stores. ----
958 assert(CopyDstReg.isVirtual() && "copy dst is not a virtual reg"); 0
959 ----
960 for (MachineInstr &UseMI : MRI->use_instructions(CopyDstReg)) { 0
961 if (UseMI.mayStore() && isInvariantStore(UseMI, TRI, MRI)) 0
962 return true; 0
963 } ----
964 return false; 0
965 } ----
966 ----
967 /// Returns true if the instruction may be a suitable candidate for LICM. ----
968 /// e.g. If the instruction is a call, then it's obviously not safe to hoist it. ----
969 bool MachineLICMBase::IsLICMCandidate(MachineInstr &I) { 0
970 // Check if it's safe to move the instruction. ----
971 bool DontMoveAcrossStore = true; 0
972 if ((!I.isSafeToMove(AA, DontMoveAcrossStore)) && 0
973 !(HoistConstStores && isInvariantStore(I, TRI, MRI))) { 0
974 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "LICM: Instruction not safe to move.\n"); 0
975 return false; 0
976 } ----
977 ----
978 // If it is a load then check if it is guaranteed to execute by making sure ----
979 // that it dominates all exiting blocks. If it doesn't, then there is a path ----
980 // out of the loop which does not execute this load, so we can't hoist it. ----
981 // Loads from constant memory are safe to speculate, for example indexed load ----
982 // from a jump table. ----
983 // Stores and side effects are already checked by isSafeToMove. ----
984 if (I.mayLoad() && !mayLoadFromGOTOrConstantPool(I) && 0
985 !IsGuaranteedToExecute(I.getParent())) { 0
986 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "LICM: Load not guaranteed to execute.\n"); 0
987 return false; 0
988 } ----
989 ----
990 // Convergent attribute has been used on operations that involve inter-thread ----
991 // communication which results are implicitly affected by the enclosing ----
992 // control flows. It is not safe to hoist or sink such operations across ----
993 // control flow. ----
994 if (I.isConvergent()) 0
995 return false; 0
996 ----
997 if (!TII->shouldHoist(I, CurLoop)) 0
998 return false; 0
999 ----
1000 return true; 0
1001 } ----
1002 ----
1003 /// Returns true if the instruction is loop invariant. ----
1004 bool MachineLICMBase::IsLoopInvariantInst(MachineInstr &I) { 0
1005 if (!IsLICMCandidate(I)) { 0
1006 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "LICM: Instruction not a LICM candidate\n"); 0
1007 return false; 0
1008 } ----
1009 return CurLoop->isLoopInvariant(I); 0
1010 } ----
1011 ----
1012 /// Return true if the specified instruction is used by a phi node and hoisting ----
1013 /// it could cause a copy to be inserted. ----
1014 bool MachineLICMBase::HasLoopPHIUse(const MachineInstr *MI) const { 0
1015 SmallVector Work(1, MI); 0
1016 do { ----
1017 MI = Work.pop_back_val(); 0
1018 for (const MachineOperand &MO : MI->all_defs()) { 0
1019 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
1020 if (!Reg.isVirtual()) 0
1021 continue; 0
1022 for (MachineInstr &UseMI : MRI->use_instructions(Reg)) { 0
1023 // A PHI may cause a copy to be inserted. ----
1024 if (UseMI.isPHI()) { 0
1025 // A PHI inside the loop causes a copy because the live range of Reg is ----
1026 // extended across the PHI. ----
1027 if (CurLoop->contains(&UseMI)) 0
1028 return true; 0
1029 // A PHI in an exit block can cause a copy to be inserted if the PHI ----
1030 // has multiple predecessors in the loop with different values. ----
1031 // For now, approximate by rejecting all exit blocks. ----
1032 if (isExitBlock(UseMI.getParent())) 0
1033 return true; 0
1034 continue; 0
1035 } ----
1036 // Look past copies as well. ----
1037 if (UseMI.isCopy() && CurLoop->contains(&UseMI)) 0
1038 Work.push_back(&UseMI); 0
1039 } ----
1040 } ----
1041 } while (!Work.empty()); 0
1042 return false; 0
1043 } 0
1044 ----
1045 /// Compute operand latency between a def of 'Reg' and an use in the current ----
1046 /// loop, return true if the target considered it high. ----
1047 bool MachineLICMBase::HasHighOperandLatency(MachineInstr &MI, unsigned DefIdx, 0
1048 Register Reg) const { ----
1049 if (MRI->use_nodbg_empty(Reg)) 0
1050 return false; 0
1051 ----
1052 for (MachineInstr &UseMI : MRI->use_nodbg_instructions(Reg)) { 0
1053 if (UseMI.isCopyLike()) 0
1054 continue; 0
1055 if (!CurLoop->contains(UseMI.getParent())) 0
1056 continue; 0
1057 for (unsigned i = 0, e = UseMI.getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) { 0
1058 const MachineOperand &MO = UseMI.getOperand(i); 0
1059 if (!MO.isReg() || !MO.isUse()) 0
1060 continue; 0
1061 Register MOReg = MO.getReg(); 0
1062 if (MOReg != Reg) 0
1063 continue; 0
1064 ----
1065 if (TII->hasHighOperandLatency(SchedModel, MRI, MI, DefIdx, UseMI, i)) 0
1066 return true; 0
1067 } ----
1068 ----
1069 // Only look at the first in loop use. ----
1070 break; 0
1071 } ----
1072 ----
1073 return false; 0
1074 } ----
1075 ----
1076 /// Return true if the instruction is marked "cheap" or the operand latency ----
1077 /// between its def and a use is one or less. ----
1078 bool MachineLICMBase::IsCheapInstruction(MachineInstr &MI) const { 0
1079 if (TII->isAsCheapAsAMove(MI) || MI.isCopyLike()) 0
1080 return true; 0
1081 ----
1082 bool isCheap = false; 0
1083 unsigned NumDefs = MI.getDesc().getNumDefs(); 0
1084 for (unsigned i = 0, e = MI.getNumOperands(); NumDefs && i != e; ++i) { 0
1085 MachineOperand &DefMO = MI.getOperand(i); 0
1086 if (!DefMO.isReg() || !DefMO.isDef()) 0
1087 continue; 0
1088 --NumDefs; 0
1089 Register Reg = DefMO.getReg(); 0
1090 if (Reg.isPhysical()) 0
1091 continue; 0
1092 ----
1093 if (!TII->hasLowDefLatency(SchedModel, MI, i)) 0
1094 return false; 0
1095 isCheap = true; 0
1096 } ----
1097 ----
1098 return isCheap; 0
1099 } ----
1100 ----
1101 /// Visit BBs from header to current BB, check if hoisting an instruction of the ----
1102 /// given cost matrix can cause high register pressure. ----
1103 bool ----
1104 MachineLICMBase::CanCauseHighRegPressure(const DenseMap& Cost, 0
1105 bool CheapInstr) { ----
1106 for (const auto &RPIdAndCost : Cost) { 0
1107 if (RPIdAndCost.second <= 0) 0
1108 continue; 0
1109 ----
1110 unsigned Class = RPIdAndCost.first; 0
1111 int Limit = RegLimit[Class]; 0
1112 ----
1113 // Don't hoist cheap instructions if they would increase register pressure, ----
1114 // even if we're under the limit. ----
1115 if (CheapInstr && !HoistCheapInsts) 0
1116 return true; 0
1117 ----
1118 for (const auto &RP : BackTrace) 0
1119 if (static_cast(RP[Class]) + RPIdAndCost.second >= Limit) 0
1120 return true; 0
1121 } ----
1122 ----
1123 return false; 0
1124 } ----
1125 ----
1126 /// Traverse the back trace from header to the current block and update their ----
1127 /// register pressures to reflect the effect of hoisting MI from the current ----
1128 /// block to the preheader. ----
1129 void MachineLICMBase::UpdateBackTraceRegPressure(const MachineInstr *MI) { 0
1130 // First compute the 'cost' of the instruction, i.e. its contribution ----
1131 // to register pressure. ----
1132 auto Cost = calcRegisterCost(MI, /*ConsiderSeen=*/false, ----
1133 /*ConsiderUnseenAsDef=*/false); 0
1134 ----
1135 // Update register pressure of blocks from loop header to current block. ----
1136 for (auto &RP : BackTrace) 0
1137 for (const auto &RPIdAndCost : Cost) 0
1138 RP[RPIdAndCost.first] += RPIdAndCost.second; 0
1139 } 0
1140 ----
1141 /// Return true if it is potentially profitable to hoist the given loop ----
1142 /// invariant. ----
1143 bool MachineLICMBase::IsProfitableToHoist(MachineInstr &MI) { 0
1144 if (MI.isImplicitDef()) 0
1145 return true; 0
1146 ----
1147 // Besides removing computation from the loop, hoisting an instruction has ----
1148 // these effects: ----
1149 // ----
1150 // - The value defined by the instruction becomes live across the entire ----
1151 // loop. This increases register pressure in the loop. ----
1152 // ----
1153 // - If the value is used by a PHI in the loop, a copy will be required for ----
1154 // lowering the PHI after extending the live range. ----
1155 // ----
1156 // - When hoisting the last use of a value in the loop, that value no longer ----
1157 // needs to be live in the loop. This lowers register pressure in the loop. ----
1158 ----
1159 if (HoistConstStores && isCopyFeedingInvariantStore(MI, MRI, TRI)) 0
1160 return true; 0
1161 ----
1162 bool CheapInstr = IsCheapInstruction(MI); 0
1163 bool CreatesCopy = HasLoopPHIUse(&MI); 0
1164 ----
1165 // Don't hoist a cheap instruction if it would create a copy in the loop. ----
1166 if (CheapInstr && CreatesCopy) { 0
1167 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Won't hoist cheap instr with loop PHI use: " << MI); 0
1168 return false; 0
1169 } ----
1170 ----
1171 // Rematerializable instructions should always be hoisted providing the ----
1172 // register allocator can just pull them down again when needed. ----
1173 if (isTriviallyReMaterializable(MI)) 0
1174 return true; 0
1175 ----
1176 // FIXME: If there are long latency loop-invariant instructions inside the ----
1177 // loop at this point, why didn't the optimizer's LICM hoist them? ----
1178 for (unsigned i = 0, e = MI.getDesc().getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) { 0
1179 const MachineOperand &MO = MI.getOperand(i); 0
1180 if (!MO.isReg() || MO.isImplicit()) 0
1181 continue; 0
1182 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
1183 if (!Reg.isVirtual()) 0
1184 continue; 0
1185 if (MO.isDef() && HasHighOperandLatency(MI, i, Reg)) { 0
1186 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Hoist High Latency: " << MI); 0
1187 ++NumHighLatency; 0
1188 return true; 0
1189 } ----
1190 } ----
1191 ----
1192 // Estimate register pressure to determine whether to LICM the instruction. ----
1193 // In low register pressure situation, we can be more aggressive about ----
1194 // hoisting. Also, favors hoisting long latency instructions even in ----
1195 // moderately high pressure situation. ----
1196 // Cheap instructions will only be hoisted if they don't increase register ----
1197 // pressure at all. ----
1198 auto Cost = calcRegisterCost(&MI, /*ConsiderSeen=*/false, ----
1199 /*ConsiderUnseenAsDef=*/false); 0
1200 ----
1201 // Visit BBs from header to current BB, if hoisting this doesn't cause ----
1202 // high register pressure, then it's safe to proceed. ----
1203 if (!CanCauseHighRegPressure(Cost, CheapInstr)) { 0
1204 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Hoist non-reg-pressure: " << MI); 0
1205 ++NumLowRP; 0
1206 return true; 0
1207 } ----
1208 ----
1209 // Don't risk increasing register pressure if it would create copies. ----
1210 if (CreatesCopy) { 0
1211 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Won't hoist instr with loop PHI use: " << MI); 0
1212 return false; 0
1213 } ----
1214 ----
1215 // Do not "speculate" in high register pressure situation. If an ----
1216 // instruction is not guaranteed to be executed in the loop, it's best to be ----
1217 // conservative. ----
1218 if (AvoidSpeculation && 0
1219 (!IsGuaranteedToExecute(MI.getParent()) && !MayCSE(&MI))) { 0
1220 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Won't speculate: " << MI); 0
1221 return false; 0
1222 } ----
1223 ----
1224 // High register pressure situation, only hoist if the instruction is going ----
1225 // to be remat'ed. ----
1226 if (!isTriviallyReMaterializable(MI) && 0
1227 !MI.isDereferenceableInvariantLoad()) { 0
1228 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Can't remat / high reg-pressure: " << MI); 0
1229 return false; 0
1230 } ----
1231 ----
1232 return true; 0
1233 } 0

1235 /// Unfold a load from the given machineinstr if the load itself could be ----
1236 /// hoisted. Return the unfolded and hoistable load, or null if the load ----
1237 /// couldn't be unfolded or if it wouldn't be hoistable. ----
1238 MachineInstr *MachineLICMBase::ExtractHoistableLoad(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
1239 // Don't unfold simple loads. ----
1240 if (MI->canFoldAsLoad()) 0
1241 return nullptr; 0
1242 ----
1243 // If not, we may be able to unfold a load and hoist that. ----
1244 // First test whether the instruction is loading from an amenable ----
1245 // memory location. ----
1246 if (!MI->isDereferenceableInvariantLoad()) 0
1247 return nullptr; 0
1248 ----
1249 // Next determine the register class for a temporary register. ----
1250 unsigned LoadRegIndex; ----
1251 unsigned NewOpc = ----
1252 TII->getOpcodeAfterMemoryUnfold(MI->getOpcode(), 0
1253 /*UnfoldLoad=*/true, ----
1254 /*UnfoldStore=*/false, ----
1255 &LoadRegIndex); ----
1256 if (NewOpc == 0) return nullptr; 0
1257 const MCInstrDesc &MID = TII->get(NewOpc); 0
1258 MachineFunction &MF = *MI->getMF(); 0
1259 const TargetRegisterClass *RC = TII->getRegClass(MID, LoadRegIndex, TRI, MF); 0
1260 // Ok, we're unfolding. Create a temporary register and do the unfold. ----
1261 Register Reg = MRI->createVirtualRegister(RC); 0
1262 ----
1263 SmallVector NewMIs; 0
1264 bool Success = TII->unfoldMemoryOperand(MF, *MI, Reg, 0
1265 /*UnfoldLoad=*/true, ----
1266 /*UnfoldStore=*/false, NewMIs); ----
1267 (void)Success; ----
1268 assert(Success && 0
1269 "unfoldMemoryOperand failed when getOpcodeAfterMemoryUnfold " ----
1270 "succeeded!"); ----
1271 assert(NewMIs.size() == 2 && 0
1272 "Unfolded a load into multiple instructions!"); ----
1273 MachineBasicBlock *MBB = MI->getParent(); 0
1274 MachineBasicBlock::iterator Pos = MI; 0
1275 MBB->insert(Pos, NewMIs[0]); 0
1276 MBB->insert(Pos, NewMIs[1]); 0
1277 // If unfolding produced a load that wasn't loop-invariant or profitable to ----
1278 // hoist, discard the new instructions and bail. ----
1279 if (!IsLoopInvariantInst(*NewMIs[0]) || !IsProfitableToHoist(*NewMIs[0])) { 0
1280 NewMIs[0]->eraseFromParent(); 0
1281 NewMIs[1]->eraseFromParent(); 0
1282 return nullptr; 0
1283 } ----
1284 ----
1285 // Update register pressure for the unfolded instruction. ----
1286 UpdateRegPressure(NewMIs[1]); 0
1287 ----
1288 // Otherwise we successfully unfolded a load that we can hoist. ----
1289 ----
1290 // Update the call site info. ----
1291 if (MI->shouldUpdateCallSiteInfo()) 0
1292 MF.eraseCallSiteInfo(MI); 0
1293 ----
1294 MI->eraseFromParent(); 0
1295 return NewMIs[0]; 0
1296 } 0

1306 /// Find an instruction amount PrevMIs that is a duplicate of MI. ----
1307 /// Return this instruction if it's found. ----
1308 MachineInstr * ----
1309 MachineLICMBase::LookForDuplicate(const MachineInstr *MI, 0
1310 std::vector &PrevMIs) { ----
1311 for (MachineInstr *PrevMI : PrevMIs) 0
1312 if (TII->produceSameValue(*MI, *PrevMI, (PreRegAlloc ? MRI : nullptr))) 0
1313 return PrevMI; 0
1314 ----
1315 return nullptr; 0
1316 } ----

1318 /// Given a LICM'ed instruction, look for an instruction on the preheader that ----
1319 /// computes the same value. If it's found, do a RAU on with the definition of ----
1320 /// the existing instruction rather than hoisting the instruction to the ----
1321 /// preheader. ----
1322 bool MachineLICMBase::EliminateCSE( 0
1323 MachineInstr *MI, ----
1324 DenseMap>::iterator &CI) { ----
1325 // Do not CSE implicit_def so ProcessImplicitDefs can properly propagate ----
1326 // the undef property onto uses. ----
1327 if (CI == CSEMap.end() || MI->isImplicitDef()) 0
1328 return false; 0
1329 ----
1330 if (MachineInstr *Dup = LookForDuplicate(MI, CI->second)) { 0
1331 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "CSEing " << *MI << " with " << *Dup); 0
1332 ----
1333 // Replace virtual registers defined by MI by their counterparts defined ----
1334 // by Dup. ----
1335 SmallVector Defs; 0
1336 for (unsigned i = 0, e = MI->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) { 0
1337 const MachineOperand &MO = MI->getOperand(i); 0
1338 ----
1339 // Physical registers may not differ here. ----
1340 assert((!MO.isReg() || MO.getReg() == 0 || !MO.getReg().isPhysical() || 0
1341 MO.getReg() == Dup->getOperand(i).getReg()) && ----
1342 "Instructions with different phys regs are not identical!"); ----
1343 ----
1344 if (MO.isReg() && MO.isDef() && !MO.getReg().isPhysical()) 0
1345 Defs.push_back(i); 0
1346 } ----
1347 ----
1348 SmallVector OrigRCs; 0
1349 for (unsigned i = 0, e = Defs.size(); i != e; ++i) { 0
1350 unsigned Idx = Defs[i]; 0
1351 Register Reg = MI->getOperand(Idx).getReg(); 0
1352 Register DupReg = Dup->getOperand(Idx).getReg(); 0
1353 OrigRCs.push_back(MRI->getRegClass(DupReg)); 0
1354 ----
1355 if (!MRI->constrainRegClass(DupReg, MRI->getRegClass(Reg))) { 0
1356 // Restore old RCs if more than one defs. ----
1357 for (unsigned j = 0; j != i; ++j) 0
1358 MRI->setRegClass(Dup->getOperand(Defs[j]).getReg(), OrigRCs[j]); 0
1359 return false; 0
1360 } ----
1361 } ----
1362 ----
1363 for (unsigned Idx : Defs) { 0
1364 Register Reg = MI->getOperand(Idx).getReg(); 0
1365 Register DupReg = Dup->getOperand(Idx).getReg(); 0
1366 MRI->replaceRegWith(Reg, DupReg); 0
1367 MRI->clearKillFlags(DupReg); 0
1368 // Clear Dup dead flag if any, we reuse it for Reg. ----
1369 if (!MRI->use_nodbg_empty(DupReg)) 0
1370 Dup->getOperand(Idx).setIsDead(false); 0
1371 } ----
1372 ----
1373 MI->eraseFromParent(); 0
1374 ++NumCSEed; 0
1375 return true; 0
1376 } 0
1377 return false; 0
1378 } ----

1380 /// Return true if the given instruction will be CSE'd if it's hoisted out of ----
1381 /// the loop. ----
1382 bool MachineLICMBase::MayCSE(MachineInstr *MI) { 0
1383 unsigned Opcode = MI->getOpcode(); 0
1384 DenseMap>::iterator CI = ----
1385 CSEMap.find(Opcode); 0
1386 // Do not CSE implicit_def so ProcessImplicitDefs can properly propagate ----
1387 // the undef property onto uses. ----
1388 if (CI == CSEMap.end() || MI->isImplicitDef()) 0
1389 return false; 0
1390 ----
1391 return LookForDuplicate(MI, CI->second) != nullptr; 0
1392 } ----

1394 /// When an instruction is found to use only loop invariant operands ----
1395 /// that are safe to hoist, this instruction is called to do the dirty work. ----
1396 /// It returns true if the instruction is hoisted. ----
1397 bool MachineLICMBase::Hoist(MachineInstr *MI, MachineBasicBlock *Preheader) { 0
1398 MachineBasicBlock *SrcBlock = MI->getParent(); 0
1399 ----
1400 // Disable the instruction hoisting due to block hotness ----
1401 if ((DisableHoistingToHotterBlocks == UseBFI::All || 0
1402 (DisableHoistingToHotterBlocks == UseBFI::PGO && HasProfileData)) && 0
1403 isTgtHotterThanSrc(SrcBlock, Preheader)) { 0
1404 ++NumNotHoistedDueToHotness; 0
1405 return false; 0
1406 } ----
1407 // First check whether we should hoist this instruction. ----
1408 if (!IsLoopInvariantInst(*MI) || !IsProfitableToHoist(*MI)) { 0
1409 // If not, try unfolding a hoistable load. ----
1410 MI = ExtractHoistableLoad(MI); 0
1411 if (!MI) return false; 0
1412 } ----
1413 ----
1414 // If we have hoisted an instruction that may store, it can only be a constant ----
1415 // store. ----
1416 if (MI->mayStore()) 0
1417 NumStoreConst++; 0
1418 ----
1419 // Now move the instructions to the predecessor, inserting it before any ----
1420 // terminator instructions. ----
1421 LLVM_DEBUG({ 0
1422 dbgs() << "Hoisting " << *MI; ----
1423 if (MI->getParent()->getBasicBlock()) ----
1424 dbgs() << " from " << printMBBReference(*MI->getParent()); ----
1425 if (Preheader->getBasicBlock()) ----
1426 dbgs() << " to " << printMBBReference(*Preheader); ----
1427 dbgs() << "\n"; ----
1428 }); ----
1429 ----
1430 // If this is the first instruction being hoisted to the preheader, ----
1431 // initialize the CSE map with potential common expressions. ----
1432 if (FirstInLoop) { 0
1433 InitCSEMap(Preheader); 0
1434 FirstInLoop = false; 0
1435 } ----
1436 ----
1437 // Look for opportunity to CSE the hoisted instruction. ----
1438 unsigned Opcode = MI->getOpcode(); 0
1439 DenseMap>::iterator CI = ----
1440 CSEMap.find(Opcode); 0
1441 if (!EliminateCSE(MI, CI)) { 0
1442 // Otherwise, splice the instruction to the preheader. ----
1443 Preheader->splice(Preheader->getFirstTerminator(),MI->getParent(),MI); 0
1444 ----
1445 // Since we are moving the instruction out of its basic block, we do not ----
1446 // retain its debug location. Doing so would degrade the debugging ----
1447 // experience and adversely affect the accuracy of profiling information. ----
1448 assert(!MI->isDebugInstr() && "Should not hoist debug inst"); 0
1449 MI->setDebugLoc(DebugLoc()); 0
1450 ----
1451 // Update register pressure for BBs from header to this block. ----
1452 UpdateBackTraceRegPressure(MI); 0
1453 ----
1454 // Clear the kill flags of any register this instruction defines, ----
1455 // since they may need to be live throughout the entire loop ----
1456 // rather than just live for part of it. ----
1457 for (MachineOperand &MO : MI->all_defs()) 0
1458 if (!MO.isDead()) 0
1459 MRI->clearKillFlags(MO.getReg()); 0
1460 ----
1461 // Add to the CSE map. ----
1462 if (CI != CSEMap.end()) 0
1463 CI->second.push_back(MI); 0
1464 else ----
1465 CSEMap[Opcode].push_back(MI); 0
1466 } ----
1467 ----
1468 ++NumHoisted; 0
1469 Changed = true; 0
1470 ----
1471 return true; 0
1472 } ----

1474 /// Get the preheader for the current loop, splitting a critical edge if needed. ----
1475 MachineBasicBlock *MachineLICMBase::getCurPreheader() { 0
1476 // Determine the block to which to hoist instructions. If we can't find a ----
1477 // suitable loop predecessor, we can't do any hoisting. ----
1478 ----
1479 // If we've tried to get a preheader and failed, don't try again. ----
1480 if (CurPreheader == reinterpret_cast(-1)) 0
1481 return nullptr; 0
1482 ----
1483 if (!CurPreheader) { 0
1484 CurPreheader = CurLoop->getLoopPreheader(); 0
1485 if (!CurPreheader) { 0
1486 MachineBasicBlock *Pred = CurLoop->getLoopPredecessor(); 0
1487 if (!Pred) { 0
1488 CurPreheader = reinterpret_cast(-1); 0
1489 return nullptr; 0
1490 } ----
1491 ----
1492 CurPreheader = Pred->SplitCriticalEdge(CurLoop->getHeader(), *this); 0
1493 if (!CurPreheader) { 0
1494 CurPreheader = reinterpret_cast(-1); 0
1495 return nullptr; 0
1496 } ----
1497 } ----
1498 } ----
1499 return CurPreheader; 0
1500 } ----

1502 /// Is the target basic block at least "BlockFrequencyRatioThreshold" ----
1503 /// times hotter than the source basic block. ----
1504 bool MachineLICMBase::isTgtHotterThanSrc(MachineBasicBlock *SrcBlock, 0
1505 MachineBasicBlock *TgtBlock) { ----
1506 // Parse source and target basic block frequency from MBFI ----
1507 uint64_t SrcBF = MBFI->getBlockFreq(SrcBlock).getFrequency(); 0
1508 uint64_t DstBF = MBFI->getBlockFreq(TgtBlock).getFrequency(); 0
1509 ----
1510 // Disable the hoisting if source block frequency is zero ----
1511 if (!SrcBF) 0
1512 return true; 0
1513 ----
1514 double Ratio = (double)DstBF / SrcBF; 0
1515 ----
1516 // Compare the block frequency ratio with the threshold ----
1517 return Ratio > BlockFrequencyRatioThreshold; 0
1518 } ----

1511 if (!SrcBF) 1511 if (!SrcBF)
1512 return true; 1512 return true;
1513 1513
1514 double Ratio = (double)DstBF / SrcBF; 1514 double Ratio = (double)DstBF / SrcBF;
1515 1515
1516 // Compare the block frequency ratio with the threshold 1516 // Compare the block frequency ratio with the threshold
1517 return Ratio > BlockFrequencyRatioThreshold; 1517 return Ratio > BlockFrequencyRatioThreshold;
1518 } 1518 }
